<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF92FFC7FF58F9A8FEABF9B3" blockId="6.[151,479,1588,1648]" box="[151,360,1623,1648]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF92FFC7FF58F9A8FED5F9B3" box="[151,278,1623,1648]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Figs 31–40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF92FFC7FEEDF9A8FEABF9B3" box="[290,360,1623,1648]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1740,1763]" captionTargetBox="[150,1435,433,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[150,1436,433,1719]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Male holotype, lateral and dorsal view: 41 – 42, Chinaia bicornis sp. nov.; 43 – 44, Chinaia longicauda sp. nov.; 45, Chinaia modesta sp. nov.; 46 – 47, Chinaia peruviana sp. nov. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272605/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">46–47</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37CDEC8FF92FFC7FF58F960FB76F8C3" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF92FFC7FF58F960FB76F8C3" blockId="6.[151,1437,1695,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF92FFC7FF58F960FED2F97B" bold="true" box="[151,273,1695,1720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pygofer with large sclerotized process arising from the middle third, dorsally curved, hook-like, with pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF92FFC7FEF3F93BFE50F91E" box="[316,403,1732,1757]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates, in ventral view, with four macrosetae medially, close to inner margin (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF92FFC7FF50F918FF37F8C3" box="[159,244,1767,1792]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus dorsally curved, “U” shaped, with fork-like bifurcated apex (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF92FFC7FBEAF918FB6AF8C3" box="[1061,1193,1767,1792]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Figs 39–40</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37CDEC8FF92FFC6FF08F8F3FB41F811" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="152" pageId="6" pageNumber="151" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF92FFC7FF08F8F3FE4CF853" blockId="6.[151,1437,1695,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF92FFC7FF08F8F3FE0BF8E6" bold="true" box="[199,456,1804,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus id="54DD33E1FF92FFC7FDDAF8F3FDBFF8E6" box="[533,636,1804,1829]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">holotype</typeStatus>
: total length 7.27; crown median length 0.52; transocular width 1.64; interocular width 0.84; frons basal width 0.60; frons length 1.04; pronotum median length 0.76; width between humeri 1.92; mesonotum median length 1.0; mesonotum maximum width 1.24; forewing length 5.96; forewing maximum width 1.36.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF92FFC6FF08F863FB8EFEA6" blockId="6.[151,1437,1695,2008]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="152" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF92FFC7FF08F863FEB2F876" bold="true" box="[199,369,1948,1973]" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">General color.</emphasis>
Pale yellow to whitish, with orange stains (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF92FFC7FCABF863FC2BF876" box="[868,1000,1948,1973]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 47" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1740,1763]" captionTargetBox="[150,1435,433,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[150,1436,433,1719]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 47. Male holotype, lateral and dorsal view: 41 – 42, Chinaia bicornis sp. nov.; 43 – 44, Chinaia longicauda sp. nov.; 45, Chinaia modesta sp. nov.; 46 – 47, Chinaia peruviana sp. nov. Scale bar = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/272605/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Figs 46–47</figureCitation>
). Head, in frontal view, pale yellow to whitish, without distinct stains, only antennal escapes light orange (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF92FFC7FC50F840FC35F81B" box="[927,1014,1983,2008]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="151">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
); crown entirely pale yellow without stains, except for conspicuous tentorial pits (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FD51FF68FD36FF73" box="[670,757,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Pronotum pale yellow with orange stripe along posterior margin not reaching lateral angles (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FDEDFF43FD67FF17" box="[546,676,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Figs 31, 33</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum pale yellow with two approximately triangular brown stains close to the lateral angles, and middle stripe of the same color that does not cross preapical fold (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FAC1FF20FA4CFF3B" box="[1294,1423,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Figs 31, 33</figureCitation>
). Forewings yellowish with yellow veins and six orange stains: one at center of clavus, one at apex of clavus, and four on basal and middle thirds, above claval suture: a basal one, two central and one preapical (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FB20FED8FA86FE83" box="[1263,1349,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Hindwing brown with red veins. Legs pale yellow to whitish with setae of the same color.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF19DDCBFF93FFC6FF58FA90FE30FA21" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152" targetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF93FFC6FF58FA90FE30FA21" blockId="7.[151,1436,1391,1506]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FF58FA90FE95FA46" bold="true" box="[151,342,1391,1414]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">FIGURES 31–40.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C66F6C0FF93FFC6FE90FA8FFDDCFA45" box="[351,543,1392,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chinaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FE90FA8FFDDCFA45" box="[351,543,1392,1414]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Chinaia peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FDE6FA8FFDBFFA46" bold="true" box="[553,636,1392,1413]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A221EC2AFF93FFC6FDE6FA8FFDBFFA46" box="[553,636,1392,1413]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male holotype: 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FCE0FA8FFC8BFA46" bold="true" box="[815,840,1392,1413]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">31</emphasis>
, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FAF2FA8FFA95FA46" bold="true" box="[1341,1366,1392,1413]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">32</emphasis>
, head, frontal view; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FEEFFA70FEFAFA67" bold="true" box="[288,313,1423,1444]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">33</emphasis>
, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FCEFFA70FCF9FA67" bold="true" box="[800,826,1423,1444]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">34</emphasis>
forewing; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FC66FA70FC01FA67" bold="true" box="[937,962,1423,1444]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">35</emphasis>
, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FAF0FA70FA9BFA67" bold="true" box="[1343,1368,1423,1444]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">36</emphasis>
, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FDC6FA52FDE1FA01" bold="true" box="[521,546,1453,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">37</emphasis>
, style, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FD3AFA52FCCDFA01" bold="true" box="[757,782,1453,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">38</emphasis>
, connective and styles, dorsal view; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FB44FA52FB67FA01" bold="true" box="[1163,1188,1453,1474]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">39</emphasis>
, aedeagus, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FF58FA33FF73FA22" bold="true" box="[151,176,1484,1505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">40</emphasis>
, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF93FFC6FF08F9F6FAADF8A5" blockId="7.[151,1437,1545,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF93FFC6FF08F9F6FE9AF9E1" bold="true" box="[199,345,1545,1570]" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Description.</emphasis>
Tentorial pits conspicuous and coronal suture indistinct; frons approximately two times its basal width; forewing about 4.5 times longer than its greatest width; anteapical cells slightly conspicuous apically. Male genitalia: in lateral view, pygofer wider basally, narrowing towards apex and without macrosetae, with large sclerotized process arising from the middle third, dorsally curved, hook-like, with pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FAFBF98AFA4CF94D" box="[1332,1423,1653,1678]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plates fused only on basal third, length about two times its basal width; in ventral view, with four macrosetae medially, close to inner margin (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FD47F942FD1EF915" box="[648,733,1725,1750]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
). Style moderately long and thickened, apex hook-like, curved ventrally and sclerotized, and with large apical lobe, lateral to hook; two microsetae bellow hook and several setae at apex of apical lobe (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FE7FF8FAFDFAF8DD" box="[432,569,1797,1822]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Figs 37–38</figureCitation>
). Connective cruciform, approximately same length of style, articulate to aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FEC2F8D6FEA3F881" box="[269,352,1833,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus dorsally curved, “U” shaped, with fork-like bifurcated apex, apical gonopore located in the middle of the bifurcation (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FDCCF8B2FD45F8A5" box="[515,646,1869,1894]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Figs 39–40</figureCitation>
). Anal tube simple, without processes (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF93FFC6FBF2F8B2FB52F8A5" box="[1085,1169,1869,1894]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="152">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). Female unknown.
</paragraph>
