</emphasis>
Right side of thorax glued to the triangle. Antennal flagellum with apical half missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF9CFFC9FF58FF68FEB8FF16" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Right foreleg with the tibia and tarsi missing; left hind leg missing. Forewings and hind wings in perfect state. Abdomen dissected.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37CDEC8FF9CFFC9FF08FF20FAA9FE44" pageId="8" pageNumber="153" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF9CFFC9FF08FF20FB6DFF34" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,392]" box="[199,1198,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FF08FF20FE8DFF3B" bold="true" box="[199,334,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Etymology.</emphasis>
