<typeStatus id="54DD33E1FF9CFFC9FBCCFF20FBABFF3B" box="[1027,1128,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F371CDD3FF9CFFC9FBBCFF1FFB69FF34" box="[1139,1194,224,247]" name="Peru" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD98D43FF9CFFC9FF08FEFBFAA9FE44" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FF08FEFBFED2FEDE" bold="true" box="[199,273,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C66F6C0FF9CFFC9FED5FEFBFE33FEDF" box="[282,496,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chinaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FED5FEFBFE33FEDF" box="[282,496,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Chinaia peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FE36FEFBFD96FEDE" bold="true" box="[505,597,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A221EC2AFF9CFFC9FE36FEFBFD96FEDE" box="[505,597,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="153" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C66F6C0FF9CFFC9FD3FFEFBFC3AFEDF" authority="Kramer" authorityName="Kramer" box="[752,1017,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chinaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepida">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FD3FFEFBFC59FEDF" box="[752,922,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Chinaia lepida</emphasis>
Kramer
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C66F6C0FF9CFFC9FBFBFEFBFA92FEDE" authority="Osborn" authorityName="Osborn" box="[1076,1361,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chinaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FBFBFEFBFB20FEDF" box="[1076,1251,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Chinaia ornata</emphasis>
(Osborn)
</taxonomicName>
in the apical processes of the pygofer (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF9CFFC9FDC6FED8FD9DFE83" box="[521,606,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
), although these processes are larger in the new species than in the later. The aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF9CFFC9FE8EFEB3FE01FEA7" box="[321,450,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Figs 39–40</figureCitation>
) is curved dorsally and “U” shaped, like in 
<taxonomicName id="4C66F6C0FF9CFFC9FC7CFEB3FBDCFEA7" box="[947,1055,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chinaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FC7CFEB3FBDCFEA7" box="[947,1055,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">C. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it does not have a long basal apodeme as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C66F6C0FF9CFFC9FEF1FE8FFE6AFE4B" box="[318,425,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chinaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FEF1FE8FFE6AFE4B" box="[318,425,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">C. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The general coloration, stains and dots of the forewing (
<figureCitation id="135D91C6FF9CFFC9FBE4FE90FBBFFE4B" box="[1067,1148,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 31 – 40" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1391,1414]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,417,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[150,1436,409,1370]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 31 – 40. Chinaia peruviana sp. nov., male holotype: 31, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 32, head, frontal view; 33, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 34 forewing; 35, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 36, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 37, style, lateral view; 38, connective and styles, dorsal view; 39, aedeagus, lateral view; 40, apex of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/165710/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) resemble 
<taxonomicName id="4C66F6C0FF9CFFC9FB38FE8FFAA0FE4B" box="[1271,1379,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Chinaia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B9125151FF9CFFC9FB38FE8FFAA0FE4B" box="[1271,1379,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="153">C. ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
